text: have you ever had chicken Kiev do you
love it how about a version that's baked
would you love it even more well if the
answer is yes then I have the recipe for
you it's baked chicken Kiev today so
what you're gonna want to do is chop up
your herbs and make an herb butter
that's going to get stuffed inside of
your chicken breast you can also toast
some bread crumbs I have these bread
crumbs here that I toasted they're panko
bread crumbs tossed with some oil and
then you toast them and till they're
golden that's actually the key to golden
delicious baked bread and things because
usually they're not in the oven long
enough in order to get golden and so if
you pre golden fi your breadcrumbs then
your baked bread and things come out
golden and delicious every time okay so
you need about two tablespoons of
parsley add it to 6 tablespoons of soft
butter and then a little bit of tarragon
and then same thing for chives but you
can use a little more like a tablespoon
of chives add the garlic straight into
your butter as well and then mash
everything together wrap it up in
plastic cause you want it to chill
before you use it so you make it into a
little log by rolling it in plastic and
get it into the refrigerator just until
it's firm and sliceable when you're
ready to cook you want to have your oven
at 425 degrees just cut into the six
side of the chicken breast not all the
way through just creating a little
pocket and I like to sort of angle my
knife down so that when you put the
butter in there and it melts in the oven
it seeps in not out then so then take
your butter that's chilled and then cut
it into four pieces then take a piece of
butter and put it into each pocket get
the butter in and then press to seal
again so if you're dredging I have a
couple of eggs seasoned that with salt
same thing with some flour about a half
a cup flour dries it off and allows the
egg to stick and then panko is the last
step and then get them onto a baking
sheet these should
take too long to bake you want to cook
these at 425 degrees until they're
cooked through about 15 to 18 minutes
there they are golden and delightful
ready for your enjoyment
